  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Montenegro: Commercial Law Judicial Training Support</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. To provide practical modules of judicial training on company law, maritime law, insolvency and consumer protection, for Montenegrin judges, so as to enable them to deal effectively with such matters; 2. To work in close collaboration with local trainers affiliated with the JTC to ensure that the training is adapted to local context; and 3. To collaborate closely with, and to the satisfaction of, the Montenegrin authorities and the EBRD Project Team</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Montenegrin Judiciary</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to enable Montenegrin judges to deal more effectively and independently with competition, intellectual property cases, insolvency, maritime law, company law and consumer protection disputes, with a particular focus on the practice of courts in the EU.</narrative>
  </description>
